===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|米|曹|ls=psc|c1=s|c2=p}}. The original version is [[𥽾]]. The radical of the rice perhaps is a reference to the liquor made out of fermented rice (see for instance [[鬯]]) and the original meaning is "unfiltered", referred for instance to liquor and wine.

